OL,3,CMichael O'Neill turns down taking
OL,4,CBlackburn Rover's role permanently
OL,6,FMichael O'Neill has confirmed he will
OL,7,Fstay on as Northern Ireland manager
OL,8,Fafter turning down the chance to take
OL,9,Fthe Blackburn Rovers job permanently.
OL,11,FThe 56-year-old finished the season
OL,12,Fjuggling both roles, having stepped in
OL,13,Fas Blackburn boss in February and
OL,14,Fsteering the club to Championship
OL,15,Fsafety with 20 points from 15 games.
OL,17,FO'Neill, however, made it clear that
OL,18,Fholding both posts long-term was not
OL,19,Fviable.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/5
