OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1778613067
OL,3,CMichael O'Neill turns down taking
OL,4,CBlackburn Rover's role permanently
OL,6,FBlackburn chief operating officer
OL,7,FSuhail Shaikh thanked O'Neill for his
OL,8,Fwork with the club.
OL,10,FSuhail Shaikh said: "Michael's
OL,11,Fexperience and leadership have been
OL,12,Fhighly valued by everyone at Blackburn
OL,13,FRovers
OL,15,F"Whilst we are naturally disappointed
OL,16,Fthat he will not be continuing on a
OL,17,Fpermanent basis, we fully respect his
OL,18,Fdecision to focus on his long-term
OL,19,Fambitions with Northern Ireland."
OL,26,@rD@UOUwD@AOU{D@aO]
