PN,39404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1778613067
OL,3,CMichael O'Neill turns down taking
OL,4,CBlackburn Rover's role permanently
OL,6,FThe Irish FA welcomed his decision,
OL,7,Fsaying: "We are delighted Michael has
OL,8,Fdecided to stay on as Northern Ireland
OL,9,Fsenior men's manager.
OL,11,F"He has built another exciting squad
OL,12,Fand we now look forward to building on
OL,13,Fthis momentum as we plan for both the
OL,14,FUEFA Nations League campaign this
OL,15,Fautumn and the subsequent qualifiers
OL,16,Ffor UEFA Euro 2028."
OL,18,FBlackburn, who will now search for
OL,19,Ftheir fourth permanent manager since
OL,20,FFebruary 2024, thanked O'Neill for his
OL,21,Fleadership and professionalism.
OL,26,@oD@IOUxD@TO]
